### 2. Pipeline Isolation Architecture

#### [NEW] `pipeline_isolator.py`

Three core classes:

**`IsolatedPipeline`** — Owns an independent `DualBlindABHarness` instance:
- Creates namespaced DB tables: `pipe_{ns}_hebbian_weight`, `pipe_{ns}_metric_log`, `pipe_{ns}_prx_decomp`, `pipe_{ns}_convergence`
- Receives regime labels from oracle via `feed_regime_labels()` (one-way, read-only)
- All Hebbian weights stay within the pipeline's own namespace

**`MotionRegimeOracle`** — Read-only regime classifier:
- Reads displacement data from ALL pipelines
- Classifies each (adapter, window_k) into 6 regimes: stationary, slow_drift, fast_drift, oscillation, jump, diffusion
- Writes ONLY to `motion_regime_oracle_log` and `motion_regime_class_diversity`
- `written_by` column is always `'oracle'` — enforced at DB level

**`run_isolated_multi_pipeline()`** — Orchestrator:
1. Phase 1: Each pipeline ingests independently
2. Phase 2: Oracle classifies regimes (read-only)
3. Phase 3: Regime labels injected → each pipeline runs isolated Hebbian A/B
4. Phase 4: Each pipeline runs isolated PRX convergence

```mermaid
graph LR
    O["MotionRegimeOracle"] -->|"read-only labels"| A["pipe_fluo"]
    O -->|"read-only labels"| B["pipe_phc"]
    O -->|"read-only labels"| C["pipe_usgs"]
    A -.->|"displacement data"| O
    B -.->|"displacement data"| O
    C -.->|"displacement data"| O
```

